<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1470,2037]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,293,1470,1494]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Description.</emphasis>
Shell ovate-elongate; right valve much more inflated than left; left valve fitting well inside right valve; anterior end broadly to sharply rounded; inequilateral, anterior end much longer; posterior end truncate, with broad, deep radial sulcus, more prominent in right valve; sculpture of fine commarginally arranged granules, densely pustulose posterior to sulcus; pallial sinus moderately wide and deep, extending past beaks; chondrophore moderately small, narrow, anteriorly directed; lithodesma small, narrow, just anterior of chondrophore. Length to 
<quantity box="[1164,1239,1598,1621]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
[
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34834" box="[1252,1355,1598,1621]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34834" name="Santa Barbara Museum of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">SBMNH</collectionCode>
].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
